snippet.textDisplay: Having not been out since last Monday for a week's supply of groceries and will have to go out tomorrow a full week from my last shop, from car into the supermarket and shop in as quick as possible time to get back home. Pay attention to wiping food items with a damp cloth of mild sterilising solution before placing them in the fridge and cupboard for you don't know how many people have been handling items searching for different items. Forward planning for family meals and sticking to your own personal meals plan for every day. Being more economical and not wasting any food. Cutting back on portion sizes and having 2 meal a day instead of 3 meals drinking less tea and coffee helps the milk last longer. Even buying a larger pack of meat like minced beef and half it using some for bolognese, cottage pie, or cornish pasty , chilli concarni. Stewed beef, casserole, potatoes and meat pie with a pastry crust. Even prepare 2 days meal at a time and place one in the fridge for the next day. By halving the meat while cooking it and making two dishes by using different ingredients. Buying bread flour and yeast and making your own bread  searching for bread recipes on the internet and people who have made videos of quick and simple step by step instructions to help you bake bread. Making your own personal pizza is not hard to do make your dough easier to do and you can use your favourite foods. My family like chopping sausages and bacon and cooking it and added to baked beans. Topped with cheese. With fries or a few chips. Buying a assortment of continental packs of meat, salami and pancetta ham, small amount of tinned tomatoes chopped and tomato paste and mixed herbs for a quick sauce for the pizza base. Vegetables pizza is simple. Buying fresh vegetables and blanching them and freeze them. Do a batch of baking, freeze some food for another time. Can't say that you have no time. For those who are staying in doors. You can be spring cleaning your own house and doing all those things that you have been putting off and not having time to do. Well you have been given the time, make the most of it. Positive thoughts and feelings less stress and anxiety.
